</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="239" pageNumber="240" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="239" pageNumber="240">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="239" pageNumber="240">
This subspecies, also known as the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Hatch’s">&quot;Hatch's</normalizedToken>
Tiger Beetle&quot;, ranges from Vancouver Island to the central region of the Sierra Nevada in California (Leffler 1987: 4).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
